HEADWORD: Confessorship
<hw>Con*fess"or*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or state of
suffering persecution for religious faith.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our duty to contend even to <qex>confessorship</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>J. H. Newman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Confestly</ent>⟦br⟧
